ENTRY       EC 3.8.1.6                  Enzyme
NAME        4-chlorobenzoate dehalogenase;
            halobenzoate dehalogenase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on halide bonds;
            In carbon-halide compounds
SYSNAME     4-chlorobenzoate chlorohydrolase
REACTION    4-chlorobenzoate + H2O = 4-hydroxybenzoate + chloride [RN:R01307]
ALL_REAC    R01307
SUBSTRATE   4-chlorobenzoate [CPD:C02370];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     4-hydroxybenzoate [CPD:C00156];
            chloride [CPD:C00698]
COMMENT     Catalyses the first step in the degradation of chlorobenzoate in Pseudomonas. In many microorganisms, this activity comprises three separate enzymes, EC 6.2.1.33 (4-chlorobenzoate---CoA ligase), EC 3.8.1.7 (4-chlorobenzoyl-CoA dehalogenase) and EC 3.1.2.23 (4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA thioesterase).
HISTORY     EC 3.8.1.6 created 1989, modified 1999
